# Testing Guidelines

## Test Stack

- **Unit tests**: Vitest (`__tests__/` directory)
- **E2E tests**: Playwright (`e2e/` directory)
- **Coverage target**: 80%+

## Running Tests

```bash
npm run test              # Vitest unit tests
npm run test:watch        # Vitest watch mode
npm run test:coverage     # Coverage report
npm run test:e2e          # Playwright E2E
npm run test:e2e:ui       # Playwright UI mode
npm run test:e2e:headed   # Playwright headed mode
```

## Unit Test Structure

```typescript
// __tests__/lib/ai/index.test.ts
import { describe, it, expect, vi } from "vitest";
import { analyzeFeeback } from "@/lib/ai";

describe("analyzeFeeback", () => {
  it("should categorize bug reports correctly", async () => {
    const mockFeedback = {
      title: "Button not working",
      description: "Click does nothing",
      type: "bug",
    };
    
    const result = await analyzeFeeback(mockFeedback, "test-api-key");
    
    expect(result.suggestedType).toBe("bug");
    expect(result.typeConfidence).toBeGreaterThan(0.8);
  });
});
```

## E2E Test Structure

```typescript
// e2e/dashboard-feedback.spec.ts
import { test, expect } from "@playwright/test";

test.describe("Feedback Dashboard", () => {
  test.beforeEach(async ({ page }) => {
    // Setup: login, navigate to dashboard
    await page.goto("/dashboard");
  });

  test("should display feedback list", async ({ page }) => {
    await expect(page.getByRole("list")).toBeVisible();
    await expect(page.getByText("Inbox")).toBeVisible();
  });

  test("should filter by type", async ({ page }) => {
    await page.getByRole("button", { name: "Bugs" }).click();
    // Assert only bugs shown
  });
});
```

## What to Test

### Unit Tests Focus On:
- Convex mutations/queries (mock ctx)
- API endpoint handlers
- Utility functions
- AI service wrappers
- Email template generation

### E2E Tests Focus On:
- Sign up and create team
- Create project and widget
- Submit feedback via widget
- View and process feedback
- Export to Linear (mocked)
- Upgrade subscription (mocked)

## Mocking External Services

```typescript
// Mock Stripe
vi.mock("stripe", () => ({
  default: vi.fn(() => ({
    customers: { create: vi.fn() },
    subscriptions: { create: vi.fn() },
  })),
}));

// Mock Resend
vi.mock("resend", () => ({
  Resend: vi.fn(() => ({
    emails: { send: vi.fn() },
  })),
}));
```

## Before Committing

```bash
npm run typecheck
npm run lint
npm run test
```

All three must pass before committing.
